Always On keep active the screen and inhibit the suspend mode simulating
a key pressure from the keyboard.
You can set which key to press and save your settings for a further
execution of the program.

You can execute the program by command line using the following
syntax (for unix based system):
java -jar <JAR PACKAGE> [OPTIONS]

Use -h option for a list of all available options.

Settings will be saved on a file in the same directory from which you
called the program. Ensure that the directory is writable before you
try to save and exit from the program.